# Stray Thought

## What am I thinking?

_Write the single core thought or observation in 1–3 sentences._

#### Master Goal
Build a 3D first-person virtual tabletop RPG platform (heavily inspired by D&D) where:

The world is primarily player- and DM-generated (lore, history, factions, locations, etc.)
Procedural generation exists only as filler / slop / inspiration / examples — never the final authority
DM and players collaboratively shape and edit the world in real time during play
Core gameplay loop is first-person open-world exploration + classic D&D-style turn-based combat
1 Dungeon Master (authoritative host) + up to 5 players
Full support for user-guided procedural generation, world creation presets by thematic style, custom rule tweaking, character creation/customization using Free5e (optionally enhanced with A5e elements)
2D SVG-based map maker (infinite zoom) that feeds into editable 3D maps powered by Terrain3D
The system stays completely agnostic to art and story content — those are 100% user responsibility

In one tight sentence:
Create an open-source(-ish) Godot-based 3D first-person VTT where the living world and its lore are built and owned by the players & DM together, with procedural generation demoted to helpful background noise, using SVG → Terrain3D maps, Free5e/A5e mechanics, and authoritative DM control.

